title: For Sale:  FN model 1906 Vest Pocket
postcontent:
This is a very collectable FN model 1906 Vest Pocket 25ACP semi-automatic handgun,  known in Europe as the Model 1905.  It is a 3rd variant model of Browning’s original patent, having a  safety catch with two notches in the slide.  The FN 1905-06 Vest Pocket is the granddaddy of all subsequent 25 ACPs, including those made later by Colt under license called the model 1908.

The 6 digit serial numbers on the frame, slide and barrel of this gun all match, beginning with 337xxx.  FN production records are irretrievable, but by one account (Eastman) 100,000 were manufactured the first year.  By July 1913 they had surpassed s/n 451,310.  In late 1913 FN made four VP 25’s with s/n’s in the 456xxx range as presentation pieces for a Jan 1914 banquet.

Interpolating between the known production numbers means this gun was probably made in 1910 or perhaps 1911.

In addition, there is a brown leather holster that fits this gun exactly.  The holster is imprinted on the back with the name and logo of Heiser Denver model 923.  Heiser had begun exporting contract holsters to Europe in the same time period as this gun was manufactured, so it’s highly likely this holster was made in small quantity specifically for the FN 1905-06.  The gun and holster together were brought from Europe to the U.S. after WWII.  They are both in pretty decent shape.  I’ve had the gun & holster for the past 50 years, which is about how long ago the gun was last fired.  

Serious buyers may call me at REDACTED.

title: For Sale:  Mossberg Maverick 88 Home Defense Package, Like-New Condition
postcontent:
For sale is a like-new Mossberg Maverick 88.  The gun comes with a complete home defense setup which makes the package worth much more than I'm selling it for.  I write detailed descriptions of the things I sell, so this isn't the ad for you if you hate reading.  But for those who prefer more than the typical 1-2 vague sentences about a firearm, then welcome.  :)

--------------------

The Gun:
This is a Mossberg Maverick 88 Special Purpose in a blued finish.  It's the 18.5" barrel version, holds up to 6 rounds (5+1), and can fire any type of 12 gauge ammo.  The full details can be found here:
http://www.mossberg.com/product/shotguns-pump-action-maverick-88-special-purpose/31023

I've had this gun for about 4 years as the first owner, and always maintained it well because it's been my primary home defense weapon.  It has only about 200 rounds through it, mostly birdshot.  Other than a few fine scratches, it has no marks, pits, deep scratches, dents, rusting, or any other kind of damage.  The bore is bright and shiny.  It's mechanically perfect and functions just as well as the first day I got it, if not better even.  Overall, I would give its condition a 95%.

As you can see, I run it with a Houge pistol grip.  This makes the shotgun extremely mobile and easy to handle, which is good for a home setting.  However, you can always switch back to the stock if you prefer.  Even with 00 buck, the recoil is very tame with the Hogue grips or the Limbsaver pad.  And although hard to see, I have a Laserlyte Shotgun Tri Rail Mount attached at the end for accessories.  If it's for home defense, a good light is a must (I'll be keeping mine however).

Overall, this is a great entry-level pump action shotgun.  It's accurate, reliable, and has served me well over the years.

--------------------

What's Included (and current prices on Amazon.com):
Hogue Pistol grip ($23)
Original stock with a Limbsaver Recoil Pad ($35)
Uncle Mike's Quick Detachable Swivel Rings ($10)
2-point sling  ($10)
Hoppe's BoreSnake Shotgun Bore Cleaner  ($13; I will wash it before selling it)
Laserlyte Shotgun Tri-Rail Mount  ($25)
Original Mossberg brand gun lock

Total = $116 in accessories

And $25 worth of ammo I'm not factoring into the price to complete the package:

2 Boxes of Royal Buck Low Recoil 00 Buckshot (10 rds total)
1 Box of Fiocchi #6 Shot (25 rds)
1 Box of Federal Truball Rifled HP Slugshot (5 rds; NOT PICTURED but will be included)

From what I see on the Internet (as of 10/3), a new Maverick will run you for about $300 (when including tax and fees), and a used one about $200-250.  When you consider all the accessories I'm including however (most of which are essential), and a 95% condition gun that has not been damaged, modified, or tacti-cooled in any way, then I would have to say this is a very good deal.  Please do the price research to make sure my claims are valid.

------------------------------

Why I'm Selling This Gun:
I recently was able to upgrade to my dream shotgun: a Benelli M4 semi-auto.  I've wanted this gun for many years, and now I finally own one.  I prefer to maintain only one shotgun, and thus selling the old Maverick.  

--------------------

Meeting/Buying Terms:
1. I currently live in Chino, CA and prefer that potential buyers meet me at the Turner's Outdoorsman in Chino Hills.
2. If you're interested in buying, please include in your message a phone number I can reach you at and the best time to call, if any.  I prefer to discuss details over phone rather than e-mail.
3. When we meet, you can fully inspect the firearm.  You won't be obligated to buy until you're satisfied with what you see.
4. I don't mind driving up to 10 miles from Chino to meet you halfway somewhere, as long as it's at a location with a FFL dealer that can do PPTs.
5. The private transfer fee at any FFL dealer is $35 ($10 transfer + $25 DROS) and the buyer will be expected to pay for that to the store as well.
6. Cash is preferred, but I'll also take Paypal if you add $9 for the 3% Paypal fee (that is, if you trust me enough to pay in advance).

--------------------

Final Notes:
1. Considering the deal on this package, the price is FIRM.
2. I'm not taking trade offers at this time.
3. I will ONLY sell to those who are willing to provide me a phone number and be able to meet me LOCALLY, in person, at a business with a FFL dealer.  Therefore, NO SHIPPING.

Please message me if there are any questions or if you're interested in buying (my name is An).  However, I will ignore any that ask to go against my terms.  There are many scammers that prowl this site, and I'm just trying to protect myself as well as the trust people put in me.  Thank you.

title: For Sale:  WARNING AL RECEIVER SPRINGFIELD SAR-8 HK CLONE = DEFECTIVE JUNK
postcontent: I am seeing multiple people trying to sell these guns on Armslist for ridiculous amounts of money. They are KNOWN DEFECTIVE junk. The steel trunnion is pinned to the cast aluminum receiver instead of welded to a steel receiver as the original designers intended. The pin hole in the aluminum receiver WILL ALWAYS ULTIMATELY FAIL allowing the trunnion to come loose in the receiver. There is no question on this it's just a matter of when and there IS NO FIX OTHER THAN TO REPLACE THE RECEIVER. This is a known fatally flawed design. The Aluminum used in the receiver simply does not have the strength needed to prevent deformation of the pin hole during use. These guns have value only for the parts. There is essentially no value as a complete firearm. Anyone is free to research this. This defect is widely known and applies only to Aluminum receiver guns. Don't get scammed out of hundreds of dollars on one of these, the Springfield name on it means NOTHING. It is the worst gun they ever put out. This defect does not apply to the Greek made SARs with stamped steel receivers ONLY to the aluminum receiver guns.
